sql:
SELECT model_name, watts
FROM heater_models
ORDER BY watts DESC;

SELECT model_name, watts, material
FROM heater_models
ORDER BY watts DESC;

SELECT model_name
FROM heater_models
WHERE watts > 5000;

SELECT COUNT(model_id)
FROM heater_models
WHERE warranty_period_months > 12;

SELECT model_name, watts
FROM heater_models
ORDER BY watts DESC;

SELECT model_name
FROM heater_models
WHERE watts = (SELECT MAX(watts) FROM heater_models);

external_knowledge:
- Top 5 best-selling models refers to the models with the highest total quantity sold; 
- Current stock levels represent the total inventory for each model; 
- Average lead times are calculated based on the lead time for each order of a model over the past year; 
- Maintenance frequencies are determined by the number of maintenance records for each model over the past year.

sql:
SELECT model_name
FROM heater_models
ORDER BY model_name ASC;

SELECT DISTINCT c.customer_name
FROM customers c
INNER JOIN sales_orders so ON c.customer_id = so.customer_id;

external_knowledge:
Heater model specifications include voltage, phase, power rating, number of heater tubes, weight, manufacturer, model year, warranty period, energy efficiency rating, operating temperature range, material, and safety certifications; 
A delivered order refers to an order that has been shipped and received by the customer;
Supplier information includes name, address, phone number, and contact email;
Recent maintenance records are sorted by the most recent maintenance date for each heater model;
Average lead time is calculated based on the average number of days between order placement and delivery for each heater model.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT model_id) AS models_below_reorder_level
FROM inventory
WHERE stock_level < reorder_level;
